The paper focuses on automated image labeling, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method also involves machine learning techniques such as generative models and affinity functions, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing techniques for designing labeling functions, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using metrics such as accuracy and compares it with existing techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
